display_long_description:
resynk is a healthcare application which involves recovery exercises for arms and hand movement.

This is done through playing video games. The games provided in this application are:

Dragon's Gold - Similar in a sense to whack-a-mole, dragons fly out of multiple dens laid out on the table before players. When players interact with the dragons (either by touching them or putting them into jars), they then score points.

Forts & Castles - Multiple fortress obstacles appear before players. Using the catapult also found in front of them, players must manipulate the catapult's aim and trajectory in order to hit the obstacles before them. Each obstacle that players destroys will award them points.

River Run - An endless runner in which players must sail up treacherous waters avoiding obstacles, collecting coins, getting mystery items and scoring points.

Zombie Slay - Players must defend themselves from waves of zombies whilst collecting points, health and brand new weaponry.

(There are NO IN-APP PURCHASES which can be found)
